\newlabel{fig:herding}{{3}{7}{Deliberation dynamics with and without information asymmetry. Left: mean per-question standard deviation of agent forecasts; right: mean pairwise inter-agent error correlation. Deliberation under homogeneous input collapses forecast diversity (herding); partitioned evidence preserves independent signal after deliberation on both datasets}{figure.caption.23}{}}
